{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890498625,"sessionID":"ses_284afa944ffeE0lGPJDv4D87g9","part":{"id":"prt_d7b52840f001lh4sQk0yKXtOps","messageID":"msg_d7b506428001jfDLiWPoGboF4Q","sessionID":"ses_284afa944ffeE0lGPJDv4D87g9","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-17a1b1922aa84e9ca03806a9a61cc326","state":{"status":"error","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# delta-spec.md — client-go 类型客户端生成\n\n**AR:** AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成  \n**Module:** client-go  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## REQ-001: Clientset Interface\n\n### REQ-001.1: Clientset Discovery Interface\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset instance created via `NewForConfig`  \n**WHEN** calling `Discovery()` method  \n**THEN** returns a `discovery.DiscoveryInterface` implementation\n\n### REQ-001.2: Clientset RuntimeV1alpha1 Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset instance  \n**WHEN** calling `RuntimeV1alpha1()` method  \n**THEN** returns a `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface` implementation\n\n### REQ-001.3: Clientset NewForConfig Constructor\n\n**GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config`  \n**WHEN** calling `NewForConfig(config)`  \n**THEN** returns a `*Clientset` with no error\n\n### REQ-001.4: Clientset NewForConfigAndClient Constructor\n\n**GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config` and `*http.Client`  \n**WHEN** calling `NewForConfigAndClient(config, httpClient)`  \n**THEN** returns a `*Clientset` using the provided HTTP client\n\n### REQ-001.5: Clientset NewForConfigOrDie Constructor\n\n**GIVEN** a valid `*rest.Config`  \n**WHEN** calling `NewForConfigOrDie(config)`  \n**THEN** returns a `*Clientset` (panics on error)\n\n### REQ-001.6: Clientset New Constructor\n\n**GIVEN** a `rest.Interface` implementation  \n**WHEN** calling `New(restClient)`  \n**THEN** returns a `*Clientset` wrapping the REST client\n\n---\n\n## REQ-002: RuntimeV1alpha1 Typed Client\n\n### REQ-002.1: RuntimeV1alpha1 RESTClient Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** a `RuntimeV1alpha1Client` instance  \n**WHEN** calling `RESTClient()` method  \n**THEN** returns a `rest.Interface` with correct GroupVersion and APIPath\n\n### REQ-002.2: RuntimeV1alpha1 GroupVersion\n\n**GIVEN** the typed client's REST client  \n**WHEN** checking configuration  \n**THEN** GroupVersion equals `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and APIPath equals `/apis`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-003: AgentRuntime Interface\n\n### REQ-003.1: AgentRuntime Create\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` for namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** creates the AgentRuntime resource and returns the created object\n\n### REQ-003.2: AgentRuntime Update\n\n**GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource  \n**WHEN** calling `Update(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** updates the AgentRuntime resource and returns the updated object\n\n### REQ-003.3: AgentRuntime UpdateStatus\n\n**GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource with modified status  \n**WHEN** calling `UpdateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** updates only the status subresource\n\n### REQ-003.4: AgentRuntime Delete\n\n**GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Delete(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`  \n**THEN** deletes the AgentRuntime resource\n\n### REQ-003.5: AgentRuntime DeleteCollection\n\n**GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources in namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `DeleteCollection(ctx, metav1.DeleteOptions{}, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** deletes all AgentRuntime resources matching the list options\n\n### REQ-003.6: AgentRuntime Get\n\n**GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns the AgentRuntime resource\n\n### REQ-003.7: AgentRuntime List\n\n**GIVEN** multiple AgentRuntime resources exist  \n**WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeList` containing all matching resources\n\n### REQ-003.8: AgentRuntime Watch\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`  \n**WHEN** calling `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns a `watch.Interface` for streaming AgentRuntime events\n\n### REQ-003.9: AgentRuntime Patch\n\n**GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Patch(ctx, \"test-ar\", types.MergePatchType, patchData, metav1.PatchOptions{})`  \n**THEN** patches the AgentRuntime resource and returns the patched object\n\n### REQ-003.10: AgentRuntime Namespace Isolation\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface` for namespace \"ns-a\"  \n**WHEN** performing any CRUD operation  \n**THEN** operations are scoped to namespace \"ns-a\" only\n\n---\n\n## REQ-004: CodeInterpreter Interface\n\n### REQ-004.1: CodeInterpreter Create\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInterface` for namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** creates the CodeInterpreter resource and returns the created object\n\n### REQ-004.2: CodeInterpreter Update\n\n**GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource  \n**WHEN** calling `Update(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** updates the CodeInterpreter resource and returns the updated object\n\n### REQ-004.3: CodeInterpreter UpdateStatus\n\n**GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource with modified status  \n**WHEN** calling `UpdateStatus(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** updates only the status subresource\n\n### REQ-004.4: CodeInterpreter Delete\n\n**GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Delete(ctx, \"test-ci\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`  \n**THEN** deletes the CodeInterpreter resource\n\n### REQ-004.5: CodeInterpreter DeleteCollection\n\n**GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources in namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `DeleteCollection(ctx, metav1.DeleteOptions{}, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** deletes all CodeInterpreter resources matching the list options\n\n### REQ-004.6: CodeInterpreter Get\n\n**GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ci\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns the CodeInterpreter resource\n\n### REQ-004.7: CodeInterpreter List\n\n**GIVEN** multiple CodeInterpreter resources exist  \n**WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterList` containing all matching resources\n\n### REQ-004.8: CodeInterpreter Watch\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInterface`  \n**WHEN** calling `Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns a `watch.Interface` for streaming CodeInterpreter events\n\n### REQ-004.9: CodeInterpreter Patch\n\n**GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Patch(ctx, \"test-ci\", types.MergePatchType, patchData, metav1.PatchOptions{})`  \n**THEN** patches the CodeInterpreter resource and returns the patched object\n\n---\n\n## REQ-005: Scheme Registration\n\n### REQ-005.1: Scheme and Codecs Initialization\n\n**GIVEN** the `clientset/versioned/scheme` package  \n**WHEN** importing the package  \n**THEN** `Scheme`, `Codecs`, and `ParameterCodec` are initialized and available\n\n### REQ-005.2: AddToScheme Registration\n\n**GIVEN** a new `runtime.Scheme`  \n**WHEN** calling `scheme.AddToScheme(scheme.Scheme)`  \n**THEN** registers all `runtime/v1alpha1` types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) to the scheme\n\n---\n\n## REQ-006: SharedInformerFactory\n\n### REQ-006.1: SharedInformerFactory New\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset and resync period of 10 minutes  \n**WHEN** calling `NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, resyncPeriod)`  \n**THEN** returns a `SharedInformerFactory` instance\n\n### REQ-006.2: SharedInformerFactory Start\n\n**GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n**WHEN** calling `Start(stopCh)`  \n**THEN** all registered informers begin syncing\n\n### REQ-006.3: SharedInformerFactory Shutdown\n\n**GIVEN** a running `SharedInformerFactory`  \n**WHEN** calling `Shutdown()`  \n**THEN** all informers stop and caches are cleared\n\n### REQ-006.4: SharedInformerFactory WaitForCacheSync\n\n**GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory` with started informers  \n**WHEN** calling `WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)`  \n**THEN** blocks until all caches are synced and returns a map of synced types\n\n### REQ-006.5: SharedInformerFactory WithNamespace\n\n**GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithNamespace(\"my-ns\")` option  \n**WHEN** creating the factory  \n**THEN** all informers are scoped to namespace \"my-ns\"\n\n### REQ-006.6: SharedInformerFactory WithTweakListOptions\n\n**GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithTweakListOptions` option  \n**WHEN** informers perform List operations  \n**THEN** the tweak function modifies ListOptions before each list call\n\n### REQ-006.7: SharedInformerFactory WithCustomResyncConfig\n\n**GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithCustomResyncConfig` option  \n**WHEN** creating the factory  \n**THEN** specific informers use custom resync periods\n\n### REQ-006.8: SharedInformerFactory WithTransform\n\n**GIVEN** `SharedInformerFactoryWithOptions` with `WithTransform` option  \n**WHEN** objects are added to the cache  \n**THEN** the transform function is applied to each object\n\n### REQ-006.9: SharedInformerFactory Runtime Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n**WHEN** calling `Runtime()` method  \n**THEN** returns the `runtime` group informer accessor\n\n---\n\n## REQ-007: Informer Group/Version Access\n\n### REQ-007.1: Runtime Group V1alpha1 Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n**WHEN** calling `Runtime().V1alpha1()`  \n**THEN** returns `v1alpha1.Interface` with informer accessors\n\n### REQ-007.2: AgentRuntime Informer Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** the v1alpha1 interface  \n**WHEN** calling `AgentRuntimes()`  \n**THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeInformer`\n\n### REQ-007.3: CodeInterpreter Informer Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** the v1alpha1 interface  \n**WHEN** calling `CodeInterpreters()`  \n**THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterInformer`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-008: AgentRuntime Informer\n\n### REQ-008.1: AgentRuntime Informer\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInformer`  \n**WHEN** calling `Informer()`  \n**THEN** returns a `cache.SharedIndexInformer` for AgentRuntime resources\n\n### REQ-008.2: AgentRuntime Lister\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInformer`  \n**WHEN** calling `Lister()`  \n**THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeLister` for listing cached AgentRuntime resources\n\n### REQ-008.3: AgentRuntime NewAgentRuntimeInformer\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset and resync period  \n**WHEN** calling `NewAgentRuntimeInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers)`  \n**THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` for AgentRuntime resources in the specified namespace\n\n### REQ-008.4: AgentRuntime NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset, resync period, and tweak function  \n**WHEN** calling `NewFilteredAgentRuntimeInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers, tweakListOptions)`  \n**THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` with custom list options\n\n---\n\n## REQ-009: CodeInterpreter Informer\n\n### REQ-009.1: CodeInterpreter Informer\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInformer`  \n**WHEN** calling `Informer()`  \n**THEN** returns a `cache.SharedIndexInformer` for CodeInterpreter resources\n\n### REQ-009.2: CodeInterpreter Lister\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInformer`  \n**WHEN** calling `Lister()`  \n**THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterLister` for listing cached CodeInterpreter resources\n\n### REQ-009.3: CodeInterpreter NewCodeInterpreterInformer\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset and resync period  \n**WHEN** calling `NewCodeInterpreterInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers)`  \n**THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` for CodeInterpreter resources in the specified namespace\n\n### REQ-009.4: CodeInterpreter NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer\n\n**GIVEN** a Clientset, resync period, and tweak function  \n**WHEN** calling `NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer(client, namespace, resyncPeriod, indexers, tweakListOptions)`  \n**THEN** creates a `SharedIndexInformer` with custom list options\n\n---\n\n## REQ-010: Generic Informer Routing\n\n### REQ-010.1: ForResource AgentRuntime\n\n**GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n**WHEN** calling `ForResource(schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"agentruntimes\"})`  \n**THEN** returns a `GenericInformer` for AgentRuntime resources\n\n### REQ-010.2: ForResource CodeInterpreter\n\n**GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n**WHEN** calling `ForResource(schema.GroupVersionResource{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\", Resource: \"codeinterpreters\"})`  \n**THEN** returns a `GenericInformer` for CodeInterpreter resources\n\n### REQ-010.3: ForResource Unknown Resource\n\n**GIVEN** a `SharedInformerFactory`  \n**WHEN** calling `ForResource` with an unknown resource  \n**THEN** returns an error indicating no informer for the resource\n\n---\n\n## REQ-011: AgentRuntime Lister\n\n### REQ-011.1: AgentRuntimeLister List\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeLister` with cached resources  \n**WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n**THEN** returns all AgentRuntime resources across all namespaces\n\n### REQ-011.2: AgentRuntimeLister List with Selector\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeLister` with cached resources labeled `app=test`  \n**WHEN** calling `List(labelSelector)` where selector matches `app=test`  \n**THEN** returns only AgentRuntime resources matching the label selector\n\n### REQ-011.3: AgentRuntimeLister Namespace Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeLister`  \n**WHEN** calling `AgentRuntimes(\"my-ns\")`  \n**THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` scoped to namespace \"my-ns\"\n\n### REQ-011.4: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister List\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` for namespace \"my-ns\"  \n**WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n**THEN** returns all AgentRuntime resources in namespace \"my-ns\"\n\n### REQ-011.5: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister Get\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` with a cached AgentRuntime named \"test-ar\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(\"test-ar\")`  \n**THEN** returns the AgentRuntime resource\n\n### REQ-011.6: AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister Get Not Found\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` without a cached AgentRuntime named \"missing\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(\"missing\")`  \n**THEN** returns an error matching `errors.IsNotFound`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-012: CodeInterpreter Lister\n\n### REQ-012.1: CodeInterpreterLister List\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterLister` with cached resources  \n**WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n**THEN** returns all CodeInterpreter resources across all namespaces\n\n### REQ-012.2: CodeInterpreterLister List with Selector\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterLister` with cached resources labeled `env=prod`  \n**WHEN** calling `List(labelSelector)` where selector matches `env=prod`  \n**THEN** returns only CodeInterpreter resources matching the label selector\n\n### REQ-012.3: CodeInterpreterLister Namespace Accessor\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterLister`  \n**WHEN** calling `CodeInterpreters(\"my-ns\")`  \n**THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` scoped to namespace \"my-ns\"\n\n### REQ-012.4: CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister List\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` for namespace \"my-ns\"  \n**WHEN** calling `List(labels.Everything())`  \n**THEN** returns all CodeInterpreter resources in namespace \"my-ns\"\n\n### REQ-012.5: CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister Get\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` with a cached CodeInterpreter named \"test-ci\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(\"test-ci\")`  \n**THEN** returns the CodeInterpreter resource\n\n### REQ-012.6: CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister Get Not Found\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` without a cached CodeInterpreter named \"missing\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(\"missing\")`  \n**THEN** returns an error matching `errors.IsNotFound`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-013: Fake Clientset\n\n### REQ-013.1: FakeClientset NewSimpleClientset\n\n**GIVEN** no pre-existing objects  \n**WHEN** calling `NewSimpleClientset()`  \n**THEN** returns a fake Clientset with an empty object tracker\n\n### REQ-013.2: FakeClientset NewSimpleClientset with Objects\n\n**GIVEN** a list of runtime objects  \n**WHEN** calling `NewSimpleClientset(objs...)`  \n**THEN** returns a fake Clientset with the provided objects in its tracker\n\n### REQ-013.3: FakeClientset Discovery\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset  \n**WHEN** calling `Discovery()`  \n**THEN** returns a fake discovery client\n\n### REQ-013.4: FakeClientset RuntimeV1alpha1\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset  \n**WHEN** calling `RuntimeV1alpha1()`  \n**THEN** returns a fake `RuntimeV1alpha1Interface`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-014: Fake Typed Clients\n\n### REQ-014.1: Fake AgentRuntime Create\n\n**GIVEN** a fake `AgentRuntimeInterface`  \n**WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** adds the AgentRuntime to the object tracker and returns it\n\n### REQ-014.2: Fake AgentRuntime Get\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset with an AgentRuntime \"test-ar\" in namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns the AgentRuntime from the tracker\n\n### REQ-014.3: Fake AgentRuntime List\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset with AgentRuntimes in namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns an `AgentRuntimeList` containing all AgentRuntimes in \"default\"\n\n### REQ-014.4: Fake AgentRuntime Update\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset with an AgentRuntime \"test-ar\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Update(ctx, modifiedAgentRuntime, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** updates the AgentRuntime in the tracker\n\n### REQ-014.5: Fake AgentRuntime Delete\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset with an AgentRuntime \"test-ar\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Delete(ctx, \"test-ar\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})`  \n**THEN** removes the AgentRuntime from the tracker\n\n### REQ-014.6: Fake CodeInterpreter Create\n\n**GIVEN** a fake `CodeInterpreterInterface`  \n**WHEN** calling `Create(ctx, codeInterpreter, metav1.CreateOptions{})`  \n**THEN** adds the CodeInterpreter to the object tracker and returns it\n\n### REQ-014.7: Fake CodeInterpreter Get\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset with a CodeInterpreter \"test-ci\" in namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `Get(ctx, \"test-ci\", metav1.GetOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns the CodeInterpreter from the tracker\n\n### REQ-014.8: Fake CodeInterpreter List\n\n**GIVEN** a fake Clientset with CodeInterpreters in namespace \"default\"  \n**WHEN** calling `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})`  \n**THEN** returns a `CodeInterpreterList` containing all CodeInterpreters in \"default\"\n\n---\n\n## REQ-015: Expansion Interfaces\n\n### REQ-015.1: AgentRuntimeExpansion Empty Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeExpansion` interface in `generated_expansion.go`  \n**WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n**THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom methods)\n\n### REQ-015.2: CodeInterpreterExpansion Empty Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterExpansion` interface in `generated_expansion.go`  \n**WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n**THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom methods)\n\n### REQ-015.3: AgentRuntimeListerExpansion Empty Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the `AgentRuntimeListerExpansion` interface in `expansion_generated.go`  \n**WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n**THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom lister methods)\n\n### REQ-015.4: CodeInterpreterListerExpansion Empty Interface\n\n**GIVEN** the `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` interface in `expansion_generated.go`  \n**WHEN** inspecting the interface definition  \n**THEN** the interface is empty (reserved for custom lister methods)\n\n---\n\n## REQ-016: Internal Interfaces\n\n### REQ-016.1: NewInformerFunc Signature\n\n**GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces.NewInformerFunc` type  \n**WHEN** inspecting the function signature  \n**THEN** it matches `func(versioned.Interface, time.Duration) cache.SharedIndexInformer`\n\n### REQ-016.2: TweakListOptionsFunc Signature\n\n**GIVEN** the `internalinterfaces.TweakListOptionsFunc` type  \n**WHEN** inspecting the function signature  \n**THEN** it matches `func(*metav1.ListOptions)`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-017: REST Resource Plural Names\n\n### REQ-017.1: AgentRuntime Resource Plural\n\n**GIVEN** an `AgentRuntimeInterface`  \n**WHEN** performing REST operations  \n**THEN** the resource plural name is `agentruntimes`\n\n### REQ-017.2: CodeInterpreter Resource Plural\n\n**GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterInterface`  \n**WHEN** performing REST operations  \n**THEN** the resource plural name is `codeinterpreters`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-018: Module Path\n\n### REQ-018.1: Module Path Correct\n\n**GIVEN** the generated client-go code  \n**WHEN** importing the module  \n**THEN** the module path is `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go`\n\n---\n\n## REQ-019: Regeneration\n\n### REQ-019.1: Make gen-client Regenerates Code\n\n**GIVEN** the source CRD definitions in `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`  \n**WHEN** running `make gen-client`  \n**THEN** executes `hack/update-codegen.sh` using `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 with `--with-watch` flag\n\n### REQ-019.2: Generated Code Matches Source Types\n\n**GIVEN** regenerated client-go code  \n**WHEN** comparing generated types against source CRDs  \n**THEN** all types in `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` are generated (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775890498617,"end":1775890498622}}}}
