{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775890504119,"sessionID":"ses_284afa944ffeE0lGPJDv4D87g9","part":{"id":"prt_d7b529997001DuILye3OYnz5av","messageID":"msg_d7b5284720012PjH17tM0yBjlG","sessionID":"ses_284afa944ffeE0lGPJDv4D87g9","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6ceb23891d0f41b1a2e2d1be5d4c313a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification: AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n2: \n3: **Module:** .github  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** L\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Purpose\n10: \n11: Automate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Pull Request Docker Build Verification\n18: \n19: The system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Docker Buildx Setup\n22: \n23: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n24: - **WHEN** the \"Agentcube CI Workflow\" job runs\n25: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL checkout the repository\n26: - **AND** set up Docker Buildx with `docker/setup-buildx-action@v3`\n27: - **AND** verify `docker --version` and `docker buildx version` outputs\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Docker Build Execution\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** Docker Buildx is configured\n32: - **WHEN** the build step executes\n33: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-build`\n34: - **AND** the job SHALL complete successfully if build passes\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ### Requirement: E2E Testing on Kind\n39: \n40: The system SHALL run `make e2e` in CI using a Kind-capable Ubuntu runner, capturing logs on failure.\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Kind Tool Installation\n43: \n44: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n45: - **WHEN** the E2E workflow runs\n46: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `helm/kind-action@v1` with `install_only: true`\n47: - **AND** Kind version SHALL be `v0.30.0`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: E2E Execution\n50: \n51: - **GIVEN** Kind tool is installed\n52: - **WHEN** the E2E test step runs\n53: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL set `ARTIFACTS_PATH=${{ github.workspace }}/e2e-logs`\n54: - **AND** use Go `1.23`\n55: - **AND** run `make e2e`\n56: \n57: #### Scenario: E2E Failure Artifacts\n58: \n59: - **GIVEN** the E2E tests fail\n60: - **WHEN** the failure handling step executes\n61: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL upload `e2e-logs` directory as artifact\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: E2E Cleanup\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** E2E tests complete (success or failure)\n66: - **WHEN** the cleanup step runs\n67: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL execute `make e2e-clean`\n68: - **AND** cleanup SHALL run even if tests fail (using `if: always()`)\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: Go Lint on Changed Go Code\n73: \n74: The system SHALL run `make lint` (golangci-lint) when Go-related paths change on pull requests to `main` or `release-*`.\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: Path Filter Configuration\n77: \n78: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n79: - **WHEN** the Lint workflow runs\n80: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `dorny/paths-filter@v3`\n81: - **AND** the `lint` filter SHALL match `**/*.go`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`, `.golangci.yml`, `.github/workflows/lint.yml`\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Lint Execution\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** path filter `lint` matches changed files\n86: - **WHEN** the lint job executes\n87: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24`\n88: - **AND** run `make lint`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Lint Skip\n91: \n92: - **GIVEN** path filter `lint` does NOT match changed files\n93: - **WHEN** the workflow evaluates the filter\n94: - **THEN** the lint job SHALL be skipped\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: ### Requirement: Code Generation Check\n99: \n100: The system SHALL verify generated artifacts match `make gen-all` when API, hack, workflow, or Makefile inputs change.\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: Codegen Path Filter\n103: \n104: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n105: - **WHEN** the Codegen Check workflow runs\n106: - **THEN** the `codegen` filter SHALL match `pkg/apis/**`, `hack/**`, `.github/workflows/**`, `Makefile`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Codegen Verification\n109: \n110: - **GIVEN** path filter `codegen` matches\n111: - **WHEN** the verification step executes\n112: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24.4`\n113: - **AND** run `make gen-check` (which runs `gen-all` and `git diff --exit-code`)\n114: - **AND** fail if generated files differ from committed version\n115: \n116: ---\n117: \n118: ### Requirement: Go Test Coverage Reporting\n119: \n120: The system SHALL run race-enabled coverage tests on `pkg/...` for qualifying pull requests and merge groups, optionally uploading to Codecov.\n121: \n122: #### Scenario: Coverage Path Filter\n123: \n124: - **GIVEN** a pull request or merge_group event\n125: - **WHEN** the Test Coverage workflow runs\n126: - **THEN** the `coverage` filter SHALL match all paths except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Coverage Test Execution\n129: \n130: - **GIVEN** path filter `coverage` matches\n131: - **WHEN** the coverage job runs\n132: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24`\n133: - **AND** run `go test -race -v -coverprofile=coverage.out -coverpkg=./pkg/... ./pkg/...`\n134: - **AND** upload `coverage.out` as artifact named `go-coverage`\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Codecov Upload\n137: \n138: - **GIVEN** `CODECOV_TOKEN` secret is configured\n139: - **WHEN** coverage tests complete successfully\n140: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL upload coverage to Codecov using `codecov/codecov-action@v4`\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Coverage Workflow Call\n143: \n144: - **GIVEN** another workflow calls `test-coverage.yml` via `workflow_call`\n145: - **WHEN** the reusable workflow is invoked\n146: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL accept optional `CODECOV_TOKEN` input\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ### Requirement: Python SDK Unit Tests\n151: \n152: The system SHALL run pytest for the SDK when `sdk-python/**` changes.\n153: \n154: #### Scenario: Python SDK Path Filter\n155: \n156: - **GIVEN** a pull request or merge_group event\n157: - **WHEN** the Python SDK Tests workflow runs\n158: - **THEN** the `sdk` filter SHALL match `sdk-python/**`\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: Python SDK Test Execution\n161: \n162: - **GIVEN** path filter `sdk` matches\n163: - **WHEN** the test job runs\n164: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Python `3.12`\n165: - **AND** set `working-directory: sdk-python`\n166: - **AND** run `pip install pytest`\n167: - **AND** run `pip install -e .`\n168: - **AND** run `python -m pytest tests/ -v`\n169: \n170: ---\n171: \n172: ### Requirement: Python Lint\n173: \n174: The system SHALL run Ruff from repository root using `pyproject.toml` when Python-touching paths change.\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Python Lint Path Filter\n177: \n178: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n179: - **WHEN** the Python Lint workflow runs\n180: - **THEN** the `python` filter SHALL match `cmd/cli/**`, `sdk-python/**`, `example/**`, `test/**/*.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Ruff Execution\n183: \n184: - **GIVEN** path filter `python` matches\n185: - **WHEN** the lint job runs\n186: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Python `3.10`\n187: - **AND** run `pip install ruff`\n188: - **AND** run `python3 -m ruff check . --config pyproject.toml`\n189: \n190: ---\n191: \n192: ### Requirement: Spelling Check (codespell)\n193: \n194: The system SHALL run codespell on the repository for pull requests to `main` or `release-*`, temporarily moving files that cause false positives.\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: False Positive File Handling\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** checkout is complete\n199: - **WHEN** codespell preparation runs\n200: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL backup/remove `pyproject.toml`, `package-lock.json`, `package.json` at repository root\n201: - **AND** find and remove nested copies of these files\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Codespell Invocation\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** false-positive files are removed\n206: - **WHEN** codespell runs\n207: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `pip install codespell`\n208: - **AND** run codespell with `--check-filenames`\n209: - **AND** use `--skip` globs for excluded paths\n210: - **AND** use `--ignore-words-list fo,nam,te,notin,NotIn`\n211: - **AND** scan the entire repository `.`\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: File Restoration\n214: \n215: - **GIVEN** codespell check completes\n216: - **WHEN** the restoration step runs\n217: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL restore all backed-up files to original locations\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ### Requirement: Copyright Header Check\n222: \n223: The system SHALL ensure `make gen-copyright` produces no git diff when applicable files change.\n224: \n225: #### Scenario: Copyright Path Filter\n226: \n227: - **GIVEN** a pull request to `main` or `release-*` branch\n228: - **WHEN** the Copyright Check workflow runs\n229: - **THEN** the `copyright` filter SHALL match all files except `*.md`, `*.svg`, `*.png`, `docs/**`, `.github/**`\n230: \n231: #### Scenario: Copyright Verification\n232: \n233: - **GIVEN** path filter `copyright` matches\n234: - **WHEN** the check job runs\n235: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL install `moreutils` package (provides `sponge`)\n236: - **AND** run `make gen-copyright`\n237: - **AND** run `git diff --exit-code`\n238: - **AND** fail if any copyright headers differ\n239: \n240: ---\n241: \n242: ### Requirement: Release Image Publication\n243: \n244: The system SHALL build and push multi-architecture images for workloadmanager, router, and picod to GitHub Container Registry on pushes to `main` and on semantic version tags.\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Tag Selection\n247: \n248: - **GIVEN** a `push` event to `main` branch\n249: - **WHEN** the build-and-push job runs\n250: - **THEN** the environment variable `TAG` SHALL be set to `latest`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: Semantic Version Tag\n253: \n254: - **GIVEN** a `push` event with tag matching `v*.*.*` or `v*.*.*-*`\n255: - **WHEN** the build-and-push job runs\n256: - **THEN** the environment variable `TAG` SHALL be set to `github.ref_name` (the tag name)\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: Registry Login\n259: \n260: - **GIVEN** the job is running\n261: - **WHEN** Docker login executes\n262: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use `docker/login-action@v3`\n263: - **AND** login to `ghcr.io` using `GITHUB_TOKEN`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Image Build and Push - Workload Manager\n266: \n267: - **GIVEN** authenticated to `ghcr.io`\n268: - **WHEN** the workload manager push step runs\n269: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push`\n270: - **AND** set `IMAGE_REGISTRY=ghcr.io/${{ github.repository_owner }}`\n271: - **AND** set `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE=workloadmanager:${TAG}`\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Image Build and Push - Router\n274: \n275: - **GIVEN** authenticated to `ghcr.io`\n276: - **WHEN** the router push step runs\n277: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-router`\n278: - **AND** set `ROUTER_IMAGE=agentcube-router:${TAG}`\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Image Build and Push - Picod\n281: \n282: - **GIVEN** authenticated to `ghcr.io`\n283: - **WHEN** the picod push step runs\n284: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL run `make docker-buildx-push-picod`\n285: - **AND** set `PICOD_IMAGE=picod:${TAG}`\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: Go Version for Release\n288: \n289: - **GIVEN** the build-and-push job runs\n290: - **WHEN** Go is set up\n291: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL use Go `1.24.4`\n292: \n293: ---\n294: \n295: ### Requirement: Dify Plugin Publish\n296: \n297: The system SHALL publish Dify plugin packages when `dify-plugin/v*` tags are pushed.\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: Dify Plugin Tag Trigger\n300: \n301: - **GIVEN** a `push` event with tag matching `dify-plugin/v*`\n302: - **WHEN** the workflow triggers\n303: - **THEN** only the `publish` job SHALL run\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Dify CLI Download\n306: \n307: - **GIVEN** the publish job runs\n308: - **WHEN** tool setup executes\n309: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL download `dify-plugin` CLI version `0.0.6`\n310: - **AND** install `yq` for YAML processing\n311: \n312: #### Scenario: Plugin Packaging\n313: \n314: - **GIVEN** tools are installed\n315: - **WHEN** packaging runs\n316: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL read `manifest.yaml`\n317: - **AND** package the plugin into `.difypkg` format\n318: \n319: #### Scenario: Cross-repo PR Creation\n320: \n321: - **GIVEN** plugin is packaged\n322: - **WHEN** publishing executes\n323: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL checkout `author/dify-plugins` repository with `GH_TOKEN`\n324: - **AND** move `.difypkg` file to target location\n325: - **AND** create branch, commit, and push\n326: - **AND** create PR to `langgenius/dify-plugins` using `gh pr create`\n327: \n328: ---\n329: \n330: ### Requirement: Workflow Approval for First-time Contributors\n331: \n332: The system SHALL optionally approve pending workflow runs for pull requests from repeat contributors or those labeled `ok-to-test`.\n333: \n334: #### Scenario: PR Target Event\n335: \n336: - **GIVEN** `pull_request_target` event on `main` or `release-**` branch\n337: - **AND** event types are `labeled` or `synchronize`\n338: - **WHEN** the Approve Workflows workflow runs\n339: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL check contributor status\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: Repeat Contributor Approval\n342: \n343: - **GIVEN** the contributor has more than one PR in the repository\n344: - **WHEN** approval logic evaluates\n345: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL list workflow runs for the head SHA with `status: action_required`\n346: - **AND** call `approveWorkflowRun` for each pending run\n347: \n348: #### Scenario: Ok-to-test Label Approval\n349: \n350: - **GIVEN** the PR has label `ok-to-test`\n351: - **WHEN** approval logic evaluates\n352: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL approve pending workflow runs even for first-time contributors\n353: \n354: #### Scenario: First-time Contributor Skip\n355: \n356: - **GIVEN** the contributor has only one PR\n357: - **AND** the PR does NOT have `ok-to-test` label\n358: - **WHEN** approval logic evaluates\n359: - **THEN** the workflow SHALL NOT approve pending runs\n360: \n361: ---\n362: \n363: ### Requirement: Workflow File Structure\n364: \n365: The system SHALL place all workflow files in `.github/workflows/` directory.\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: Workflow Directory\n368: \n369: - **GIVEN** the `.github` module is implemented\n370: - **WHEN** checking the directory structure\n371: - **THEN** all workflow YAML files SHALL be in `.github/workflows/`\n372: \n373: #### Scenario: Workflow Naming Convention\n374: \n375: - **GIVEN** workflow files are created\n376: - **WHEN** naming workflows\n377: - **THEN** workflow filenames SHALL use lowercase with hyphens (e.g., `main.yml`, `e2e.yml`, `lint.yml`)\n378: - **AND** workflow `name` fields SHALL use descriptive titles (e.g., \"Agentcube CI Workflow\", \"Lint\")\n379: \n380: ---\n381: \n382: ## Implementation Files\n383: \n384: | File | Purpose |\n385: |------|---------|\n386: | `.github/workflows/main.yml` | Pull request Docker build verification |\n387: | `.github/workflows/e2e.yml` | End-to-end tests on Kind cluster |\n388: | `.github/workflows/lint.yml` | Go lint with path filtering |\n389: | `.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml` | Python SDK pytest execution |\n390: | `.github/workflows/python-lint.yml` | Python Ruff lint check |\n391: | `.github/workflows/test-coverage.yml` | Go test coverage with Codecov upload |\n392: | `.github/workflows/codegen-check.yml` | Code generation drift verification |\n393: | `.github/workflows/copyright-check.yml` | Copyright header consistency check |\n394: | `.github/workflows/codespell.yml` | Spelling check with false-positive handling |\n395: | `.github/workflows/build-push-release.yml` | Multi-arch image build and push to GHCR |\n396: | `.github/workflows/dify-plugin-publish.yml` | Dify plugin packaging and cross-repo PR |\n397: | `.github/workflows/workflows-approve.yml` | Workflow approval for trusted contributors |\n398: \n399: ---\n400: \n401: ## Dependencies\n402: \n403: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n404: |------------|---------|---------|\n405: | `dorny/paths-filter` | v3 | Path-based job filtering |\n406: | `docker/setup-buildx-action` | v3 | Docker Buildx setup |\n407: | `docker/login-action` | v3 | Container registry authentication |\n408: | `helm/kind-action` | v1 | Kind cluster tooling |\n409: | `actions/setup-go` | v5 | Go runtime setup |\n410: | `actions/setup-python` | v5 | Python runtime setup |\n411: | `codecov/codecov-action` | v4 | Coverage upload |\n412: | `actions/github-script` | v7 | GitHub API scripting |\n413: \n414: ---\n415: \n416: ## Validation Checklist\n417: \n418: - [ ] `main.yml` builds Docker image on PR to `main` or `release-*`\n419: - [ ] `e2e.yml` runs `make e2e` with Kind v0.30.0, uploads logs on failure\n420: - [ ] `lint.yml` path-filters for Go files and runs `make lint`\n421: - [ ] `python-sdk-tests.yml` runs pytest in `sdk-python/` directory\n422: - [ ] `python-lint.yml` runs Ruff with `pyproject.toml` config\n423: - [ ] `test-coverage.yml` runs race-enabled coverage tests, uploads to Codecov\n424: - [ ] `test-coverage.yml` supports `workflow_call` with optional `CODECOV_TOKEN`\n425: - [ ] `codegen-check.yml` path-filters and runs `make gen-check`\n426: - [ ] `copyright-check.yml` path-filters and runs `make gen-copyright`\n427: - [ ] `codespell.yml` handles false-positive files and restores them\n428: - [ ] `build-push-release.yml` pushes to `ghcr.io` on `main` push and version tags\n429: - [ ] `build-push-release.yml` sets `TAG=latest` for main, `TAG=tag-name` for tags\n430: - [ ] `dify-plugin-publish.yml` triggers on `dify-plugin/v*` tags\n431: - [ ] `workflows-approve.yml` approves runs for repeat contributors or `ok-to-test` label\n432: - [ ] All 12 workflow files exist in `.github/workflows/`\n433: - [ ] Workflow names follow descriptive naming convention\n\n(End of file - total 433 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification: AR-034 — CI/CD GitHub Actions (12 workflows)\n\n**Module:** .github  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nAutomate validation on pull requests (build, lint, tests, codegen drift checks), publish container images on pushes to `main` and version tags, run end-to-end tests on Kind, exercise the Python SDK, and enforce spelling and copyright consistency.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Pull Request Docker Build Verification\n\nThe system SHALL build the Workload Manager Docker image on pull requests targeting `main` or `release-*` branches.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775890504102,"end":1775890504116}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775890504136,"sessionID":"ses_284afa944ffeE0lGPJDv4D87g9","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5299b6001bkoD4zqdFbHno4","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7b5284720012PjH17tM0yBjlG","sessionID":"ses_284afa944ffeE0lGPJDv4D87g9","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":24177,"input":5648,"output":80,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":18449}},"cost":0}}
